{
  "text": "Second, in many change detection studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , it has been found that location is a special feature, which induces a different behavioral pattern than the other features. Processing surface features (e.g., color, shape) is automatically bound to a spatial position [CITATION_4] . Location processing is of unlimited capacity and is completed in a parallel fashion at the pre-attentive stage [CITATION_5] . Accordingly, we may speculate that the irrelevant spatial relation can aid color change detection because of its unique role in perception and memory. As such, our ongoing study is designed to test the effect of task relevancy on relational processing in VSTM when both task-relevant and task-irrelevant relational information are of different featural relations.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2280319",
